Kenya and St Kitts and Nevis yesterday signed a joint communiqu&eacute; to establish diplomatic relations.It was signed at the sidelines of the 71st Session of the UN General Assembly in New York by Foreign Affairs CS Amina Mohamed (pictured) and her St Kitts and Nevis counterpart Mark Brantley.&ldquo;This is an important first step and we look forward to further engagements that will lay down a structured framework of cooperation,&rdquo; Mohamed said.